reviews.review_text: Thanks for the Aud! your recording makes this show worth listening to.  I was at this Spectrum run and felt that musically this night contained most of the highlights...but listening to the SBD only made me cringe.  The response to the C.C. Rider morph into Train to Cry gets no respect on the SBD, but here it's all clear - mirthful joy at the spontaneity of it all.  The ambiance from the audience helps put it all back in context and with the proper place and setting I can enjoy again the twilight of the Dead.  So 4 stars - not because this is a mindbender of a show but because (as with many of the shows from this time) it shows glimpses of what was and what could have been.

Kicks the SBD's ass But there's an abrupt cut in Drums going into space.  Although the other AUD has the same cut, I don't think the Powers That Be would object to a minute or two patch from the SBD being posted here - there are other sources containing minor SBD patches on this site that are downloadable, and should be.  Anyway, anyone so inclined can use the board to patch this segment.

That said, this is an incredible source.
- Kinda jamless, apart from the Space.
